{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"CHARACTERIZATION COMPLETE (2026-07-11): rebar's structured-output path is NOT vulnerable to refusal-as-content on the current stack. Determination: pydantic-ai 1.107.0's Anthropic model (models/anthropic.py) maps Anthropic stop_reason='refusal' -> finish_reason='content_filter' via _FINISH_REASON_MAP (line 95) and sets it on the ModelResponse (lines 951-953), also stashing the refusal explanation in provider_details['refusal'] (line 957). rebar's structured.check_stop_reason treats BOTH 'refusal' and 'content_filter' as _UNRETRYABLE_STOP_REASONS, and the runner calls it on BOTH output paths (runner.py NativeOutput + PromptedOutput) BEFORE returning/parsing output. So a refusal already raises UnretryableOutputError -> the gate degrades to INDETERMINATE, never a hollow PASS. The #5221 gap (refusal as content with a benign finish_reason) does NOT reproduce here because pydantic-ai populates finish_reason from stop_reason. Cites pydantic-ai #5221 / #6167. RESOLUTION = characterized-not-vulnerable, with two hardening additions per the fail-closed decision: (1) a NEW structured.check_response(response) that layers a defense-in-depth read of provider_details (raw 'refusal'/'finish_reason') on top of check_stop_reason, so rebar stays fail-closed EVEN IF a future adapter stops mapping a refusal onto finish_reason (the exact #5221 shape); the runner now calls check_response on both paths. (2) A regression/contract test (tests/unit/test_refusal_as_content.py) that imports pydantic-ai's _FINISH_REASON_MAP and asserts Anthropic 'refusal' still maps into rebar's catch set — so a future pydantic-ai remap that would silently reopen the gap FAILS the test loudly. Verified: 7 new tests + silent-success/structured/llm-failure suites (139 tests) pass; ruff + mypy clean."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783813169586783001,"uuid":"c5763534-8c17-4058-ae0d-9399e0ac3b1e"}